  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing UNIDO#s strategic approach with a view to harmonizing the Organization#s programmatic response and strengthening the field network capacity</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The new programme for country partnership (PCP) approach adopted by UNIDO was widely supported by Member States that would like to see this innovative modality being further expanded to cover more countries. The solid interest showed by key development partners and the experience gained in formulating and launching the first PCPs shows that this programming modality is now mature to enter its second phase that will allow UNIDO&apos;s integrated services to be further extended. In particular, proposals are to be developed to expand and implement the partnership approach. This will imply innovative approaches to integrated services delivery.

Moreover, UNIDO&#x2019;s Country Programmes (CP) and intra-regional programmes remain strategic instruments to foster ISID on the ground. Under the right conditions and with the appropriate operational modalities, the CP have the potential to be upgraded to PCP. Therefore, the need has been identified to further expand and harmonize UNIDO&#x2019;s programmatic approach. Under this project, one of the intended results is a proposal to the UNIDO Senior Management on how to establish a unified operational approach for programme development.

At the same time, the recent restructuring of the field network resulting from the reduction of regular budget has diminished the resources for outreach capacity of the Organization and the support that the field network can provide to the TC-activities, from formulation to implementation.  Hence, the increased demand for UNIDO services requires that resources and competences are used more effectively and that the coordination between field network and Headquarters is further strengthened. In particular, proposals are to be developed on how in-house technical expertise will be best combined with field office resources to foster an integrated and effective approach to UNIDO&#x2019;s service delivery.

The project aims at providing advice and support to the Director General and UNIDO&#x2019;s management on major strategic areas. In close coordination and cooperation with the Managing Directors and other senior officials, the project will support the UNIDO&#x2019;s outreach activities with a view to ensuring the efficient and effective implementation of its mandate. Furthermore, in view of the cross organizational nature of this project, a thorough knowledge of UNIDO&#x2019;s core functions and a good understanding of the strategic orientation of the executive management, are required.</narrative>
  </description>
